A police officer on Wednesday shot dead his wife and their five-year-old daughter after a domestic quarrel. The officerÂ had an argument with his wife before he picked his gun and shot her in the head at the Anti-Stock Theft Unit camp in Subukia, Nakuru. He then turned the gun on his daughter before escaping. Police say a manhunt for the officer is ongoing. Elsewhere, a 45-year-old man was lynched by a mob on allegations he had killed his girlfriend inside a matatu in Buruburu, Nairobi. The man had quarrelled with the woman in the matatu before he reportedly stabbed her to death. As he tried to escape from the vehicle, a mob chased and stoned him to death. It is not clear what prompted the quarrel.  Click here for the latest political   